# Automation Project for Falabella.com using Selenium Java and Cucumber

This is a Maven project that uses Cucumber and Selenium Java for test automation. The project is designed to automate the following tests for the website [www.falabella.com](http://www.falabella.com):

1. Search for a product using the categories of the site.
2. Validate that the price of a product matches the total in the shopping cart.

## Dependencies

The project uses the following Maven dependencies:

```xml
<dependency>
  <groupId>io.cucumber</groupId>
  <artifactId>cucumber-java</artifactId>
  <version>7.0.0</version>
  <scope>test</scope>
</dependency>

<dependency>
  <groupId>io.cucumber</groupId>
  <artifactId>cucumber-junit</artifactId>
  <version>7.0.0</version>
  <scope>test</scope>
</dependency>

<dependency>
  <groupId>org.seleniumhq.selenium</groupId>
  <artifactId>selenium-java</artifactId>
  <version>4.1.0</version>
  <scope>test</scope>
</dependency>

<dependency>
  <groupId>junit</groupId>
  <artifactId>junit</artifactId>
  <version>4.12</version>
  <scope>test</scope>
</dependency>

```
## io.cucumber:cucumber-java
Cucumber-Java is a library that allows you to define feature files and their corresponding step definitions in Java. It is an implementation of the Cucumber testing framework and enables behavior-driven development (BDD) testing.

## io.cucumber:cucumber-junit
Cucumber-Junit is an integration of Cucumber with JUnit, a popular testing framework for Java. It allows you to run Cucumber tests using the JUnit test runner, which is included in most Java IDEs.

## org.seleniumhq.selenium:selenium-java
Selenium is a popular open-source automation tool used for web application testing. It provides a WebDriver API for interacting with web browsers such as Chrome, Firefox, and Edge. The selenium-java dependency includes all the necessary files for running Selenium tests in Java.

## junit:junit
JUnit is a popular testing framework for Java. It provides annotations for defining test methods, assertions for verifying test results, and a test runner for executing tests. The junit dependency is used for running the Cucumber tests as JUnit tests.

## Installation
1. Install Java 8 or above.
2. Install Maven.
3. Clone the repository to your local machine:  `git clone https://github.com/felipebustosp/automation-framework-falabella.git`
4. Open a terminal and navigate to the root directory of the project.
4. Run the following command to build the project and download the necessary dependencies:
``` mvn clean install ```

## Usage
To run the tests, simply execute the following command in the terminal:

```mvn test```

The tests will be run automatically and the results will be displayed in the console.

